"[1] (15w) Brew: A family of 7 sits down to eat some leftovers for dinner one evening.
[2] (13w) They’ve saved some pasta salad from a picnic they had on the weekend.
[3] (30w) It smells a little funny, so three of the children only eat a small portion, but it would be wasteful to throw it away, so it should be fine, right?
[4] (14w) Unfortunately not, for in a short 6 hours all 5 children will be hospitalized.
[5] (35w) After what everyone thought was just a simple dinner, finishing off some leftovers to make sure nothing was wasted, quickly devolved into bouts of vomiting, laboured breathing, and a fight for their children’s very lives.
[6] (4w) Let’s get into it!
[7] (28w) After a picnic in the park on a Friday circa 2003, 5 children became sick after eating leftover pasta salad their family had saved until the following Monday.
[8] (25w) The salad smelled funny, so three of the kids, two girls aged 9 and 10, and a boy, aged 14, only ate a little bit.
[9] (16w) Shortly after finishing the salad, about 6 hours later, the youngest girl, aged 7, began vomiting.
[10] (5w) Suddenly, her breathing became labored.
[11] (27w) She was taken immediately to the emergency room of a local hospital, but as they arrived, the rest of the children began to throw up as well.
[12] (23w) The youngest girl and her 9 year old brother’s breathing worsened quickly, so medical staff intubated them and got them on mechanical ventilators.
[13] (45w) All of the children were then transported to the University Hospital in Leuven, but during transfer, the youngest girl experienced a severe pulmonary hemorrhage, which meant that blood was leaking into her airways, and paramedics were forced to apply continuous resuscitation to keep her alive.
[14] (11w) When she arrived at the Leuven hospital, she was near death.
[15] (10w) In a coma, with internal bleeding, and intense muscle cramps.
[16] (27w) Unfortunately, there was nothing doctors could do, and she died after 20 minutes of arriving at the university hospital, only 13 hours after eating the pasta salad.
[17] (16w) The salad was made on a Friday, before being taken to the picnic the next day.
[18] (21w) Unfinished, they brought the salad home and kept it in the fridge until Monday night when it was served to everyone.
